<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="053" project="ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Action Template — "Summarize a matter" (Deterministic Dataverse query + AI narrative summary)</title>
    <phase>Phase 5: Surfaces + Templates</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>4</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>040, 041, 052</dependencies>
    <blocks>060</blocks>
    <tags>dataverse, ai, deploy</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>JPS Action JSON authoring + Dataverse seed. Produces the "Conservative 3" Template #1 per spec.md FR-19. No new C# code; deliverable is a JPS-validated JSON definition + a deploy invocation. Has explicit ADR constraints (013, 015, 018) and dependencies (040, 041, 052).</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>E</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Independent JPS JSON authoring; no file overlap with tasks 054, 055 (each writes to its own `infra/insights/schemas/template-*.json`). Same prerequisite set (040 + 041 + 052). Safe for parallel sub-agent execution.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Author the "Summarize a matter" Action Template as a JPS-compliant JSON definition at `infra/insights/schemas/template-summarize-matter.json` and seed it into Dataverse (`sprk_actiontemplate` entity). Per spec.md FR-19 + design.md "Conservative 3", this is a Hybrid two-step Action: (Step 1) Deterministic `QueryDataverse` Tool fetches a matter rollup — status, key dates, recent activity, open tasks, active counterparties; (Step 2) AI Tool composes a narrative multi-paragraph summary grounded in step 1's output. Default `humanGate.required = false` for the summary itself; output routes to chat surface AND offers an optional `SendEmail` Tool (which requires gate) as a follow-up Action. Validates against the JPS schema via the `jps-validate` skill before deployment.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Spaarke AI Template author with deep familiarity with the JPS (JSON Prompt Schema) Action definition format, the `jps-action-create` + `jps-validate` skills, the Tool Registry contract from task 020 (Classification / CostClass / LatencyClass / EvidenceRequired / SourceCitations), and the default `Spaarke Assistant — General` playbook seeded in task 052. You author with discipline — the LLM-facing Tool descriptions ARE contracts (design.md §7.4.5 guardrail #2).
  </role>

  <goal>
    Three concrete outcomes:
    1. **JPS Action JSON** — `infra/insights/schemas/template-summarize-matter.json` with `instruction`, `output` field schema (multi-paragraph narrative + `sourceCitations` array), `scopes` (the matter record id input parameter), `templateParams` (optional rollup-depth, lookback window), and at least one `examples` block. Wires Step 1 (Deterministic `QueryDataverse` for matter rollup) → Step 2 (AI `SummarizeText` Tool with the rollup as evidence).
    2. **Dataverse seed** — upsert `sprk_actiontemplate` row pointing at this JSON. Parameter schema published. References the default playbook from task 052 (system prompt inherited).
    3. **E2E test seed** — a worked example invocation: "Summarize Matter X" via SpaarkeAi chat resolves to this Template via `FindResources`, runs both steps, returns the narrative with source citations. This is the **G2 acceptance gate** (conversational invocation resolves user intent → Tool).

    Deliverable: `infra/insights/schemas/template-summarize-matter.json`, a deploy invocation recorded in `notes/deploys/053-template-summarize-matter.md`, and a verification of the JPS schema via `jps-validate`.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Spec.md FR-19 mandates the "Summarize a matter" Template. Design.md §10 "Phased Delivery" + "Conservative 3" decision (owner clarification table) confirms this as MVP Template #1. The output routes to the SpaarkeAi chat surface; the optional `SendEmail` follow-up Tool (which requires gate per `IGateResolver` rules) is exposed in the result tile as a button — but the email itself is NOT in this Template; it's invoked separately by the user.

      Spec.md Success Criterion #2: "Conversational invocation via SpaarkeAi Code Page resolves user intent → Tool via meta-tools and executes. **Verify**: E2E test with 'Summarize Matter X' yielding the matter's summary in chat with citations." — this is the **G2 acceptance gate**. This Template is the test subject for G2.

      The Template's `EvidenceRequired: true` flag (design.md §7.4.5 guardrail #3) means the AI `SummarizeText` step MUST NOT produce a summary without supporting evidence from Step 1's deterministic query. The Tool dispatch layer (`IToolHandlerRegistry`) enforces this — runtime guard, not prompt-coached.

      Per ADR-015, every Tool dispatch this Template makes writes audit (Tier 2 hash-only + Tier 3 Cosmos work history with tenant scoping). The Template authors do NOT add audit code — `AuditEnrichmentMiddleware` (task 044) is the choke point. This task's responsibility is only to ensure the Template's JSON contract correctly identifies which Tool dispatches happen (so audit can fingerprint them).

      Per ADR-018, this Template's governance block MUST reference a feature flag (e.g., `feature.actionEngine.template.summarizeMatter`) so it can be disabled per environment.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>infra/insights/schemas/template-summarize-matter.json</file>
      <file>infra/insights/schemas/playbook-spaarke-assistant-general.json</file>
      <file>scripts/Seed-JpsActions.ps1</file>
      <file>projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/notes/deploys/053-template-summarize-matter.md</file>
      <file>projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/design.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">AI placement: Template lives in Dataverse + `infra/insights/schemas/`; BFF reads via `Services/Ai/PublicContracts/` facade. No CRUD-side caller injects `IActionTemplateService` or other internals.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Audit on every Tool dispatch this Template makes (Tier 2 hash + Tier 3 work history). This task authors the Template; the audit machinery (task 044 `AuditEnrichmentMiddleware`) does the writing. Verify the Template's Tool ids match what audit will fingerprint.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-018">Feature flag: `feature.actionEngine.template.summarizeMatter` referenced in the Template's `governance` block per spec.md §5 "Governance" field.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Publish size impact: Templates are JSON, low impact. Adds NO BFF code, NO new NuGet. Zero publish-size delta.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Validate the JPS JSON via `jps-validate` skill BEFORE seeding to Dataverse. Schema violations halt deployment.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">`EvidenceRequired: true` on the AI summarize step. Tool dispatch layer enforces this.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Tool description for the `SummarizeMatter` Action is the LLM-facing contract (design.md §7.4.5 guardrail #2). Write it as a precise interface declaration: "Summarize the open status, key dates, recent activity, and active counterparties of a specific matter record. Input: matter record id. Output: multi-paragraph narrative with source citations to the underlying Dataverse records."</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Default `humanGate.required = false` for the summary itself. The optional `SendEmail` follow-up Action (which DOES require gate) is NOT part of this Template — it's a separate Action surfaced as a follow-up button in the result tile.</constraint>
  </constraints>

