    <patterns>
      <pattern name="JPS Action authoring workflow" location=".claude/skills/jps-action-create/SKILL.md">Canonical workflow: define instruction, output schema, scopes, templateParams, examples. Validate before deploy.</pattern>
      <pattern name="Tool description as contract" location="projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/design.md §7.4.5">Tool descriptions ARE the LLM-facing interface declaration. Write with precision.</pattern>
      <pattern name="Evidence-required runtime guard" location="projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/design.md §7.4.5">Inference Tools with `EvidenceRequired: true` MUST receive supporting evidence in the dispatch payload or the dispatch is rejected.</pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="0">Context check: confirm working tree clean, dependencies (tasks 040 Action endpoints, 041 orchestration service, 052 default playbook) marked ✅ in `TASK-INDEX.md`. (task-execute Step 0)</step>
    <step order="1">Read all files in `&lt;knowledge&gt;&lt;files&gt;` — especially spec.md FR-19, design.md §7.4.5 (8 guardrails), the `jps-action-create` skill workflow, and the seeded playbook from task 052 (system prompt inheritance).</step>
    <step order="2">Use the `jps-action-create` skill to scaffold the Template JSON. Populate:
      - `instruction`: brief LLM-facing description of the Template's purpose
      - `scopes`: `[{name: "matterId", type: "guid", required: true, sourceHints: ["surface", "ask"]}]`
      - `templateParams`: `[{name: "lookbackDays", type: "int", default: 30}, {name: "rollupDepth", type: "enum", values: ["concise", "detailed"], default: "concise"}]`
      - `steps`:
        - Step 1: `{tool: "QueryDataverse", params: {entity: "sprk_matter", id: "{matterId}", related: ["sprk_task", "sprk_event", "contact"], lookbackDays: "{lookbackDays}"}}` — Deterministic, no gate
        - Step 2: `{tool: "SummarizeText", params: {evidence: "{step1.output}", style: "narrative", depth: "{rollupDepth}"}, evidenceRequired: true}` — AI, no gate, requires evidence from step 1
      - `output`: schema for `{narrative: string, sourceCitations: [{recordId, entityType, fieldName}]}`
      - `examples`: at least one worked example with input/output pair
      - `governance.featureFlag`: `"feature.actionEngine.template.summarizeMatter"`
      - `governance.killSwitch`: `false`
    </step>
    <step order="3">Run the `jps-validate` skill against the JSON. Halt on schema violations; fix and re-validate.</step>
    <step order="4">Deploy via `scripts/Seed-JpsActions.ps1` (or equivalent — verify via `Glob`): upsert `sprk_actiontemplate` row keyed by `sprk_name = 'summarize-matter'`. Capture stdout/stderr to `notes/deploys/053-template-summarize-matter.md`.</step>
    <step order="5">**Verification** — execute the Template manually via the BFF `/run` endpoint (POST /api/actions/run with `{templateId: 'summarize-matter', parameters: {matterId: '&lt;dev-matter-guid&gt;'}}`). Confirm:
      - The Run record is created in `sprk_actionrun` with `Queued → Running → Completed` status sequence
      - Step 1 (QueryDataverse) audit row exists (Tier 2 hash)
      - Step 2 (SummarizeText) audit row exists with `EvidenceRequired: true` honored (dispatch payload included step 1's output)
      - Output narrative contains source citations referring to the matter's actual records
    </step>
    <step order="6">**G2 acceptance gate** — verify conversational invocation via SpaarkeAi resolves user intent → Tool (E2E test: "Summarize Matter X" — G2 per spec.md Success Criterion #2):
      - Open SpaarkeAi Code Page (no-context landing)
      - Type "Summarize Matter X" (using a real matter name from the dev environment)
      - Verify the agent calls `FindResources("summarize matter X")` → returns the `summarize-matter` Template id with high confidence
      - Verify the agent calls `GetResourceDetail("summarize-matter")` → returns the parameter schema
      - Verify the agent resolves `matterId` via `QueryDataverse` (entity lookup by name)
      - Verify the agent calls `InvokeResource("summarize-matter", {matterId: "..."})` → runs the Template
      - Verify the summary appears in chat with source citations
      Capture the run id + audit record ids in `notes/deploys/053-template-summarize-matter.md` as evidence for the G2 gate.
    </step>
    <step order="7">**Idempotency verification**: re-run the seed script. Confirm record count = 1 (no duplicate).</step>
    <step order="8">Update `current-task.md` with progress; checkpoint via `context-handoff` skill.</step>
    <step order="9">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 053 status ✅. Note the G2 gate verification evidence in the project's "Decisions" or "Acceptance Evidence" appendix.</step>
    <step order="10">If any deviations from this plan, document in `projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/notes/handoffs/053-deviations.md`.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="jps-action-create">Scaffold the JPS Action JSON</tool>
    <tool name="jps-validate">Validate JSON against JPS schema</tool>
    <tool name="dataverse-deploy">Upsert `sprk_actiontemplate` row</tool>
    <tool name="powershell">Run Seed-JpsActions.ps1</tool>
    <tool name="curl">Invoke BFF `/run` endpoint for verification</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="data">infra/insights/schemas/template-summarize-matter.json</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/notes/deploys/053-template-summarize-matter.md</output>
    <output type="dataverse-record">`sprk_actiontemplate` row `summarize-matter` in dev environment</output>
    <output type="evidence">G2 gate verification (conversational invocation E2E test result)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md (status update)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/current-task.md (status update)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`infra/insights/schemas/template-summarize-matter.json` exists and passes the `jps-validate` schema check.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">The Template's Step 2 (`SummarizeText`) has `EvidenceRequired: true` and references Step 1's output as evidence.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">The Template's `governance.featureFlag` references `feature.actionEngine.template.summarizeMatter`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">After deployment, exactly one `sprk_actiontemplate` row with `sprk_name='summarize-matter'` exists in the dev environment. Re-running the seed yields no duplicate.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Manual invocation via BFF `/run` endpoint completes with status `Completed`; both audit rows (Tier 2 for each Tool dispatch) exist.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">**G2 acceptance gate**: Conversational invocation via SpaarkeAi resolves user intent → Tool (E2E test: 'Summarize Matter X' — G2). Verified by an interactive session with a real matter name; summary appears in chat with citations.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">The output narrative includes `sourceCitations` array referring to underlying Dataverse record ids (citation discipline per design.md §7.4.5 guardrail #7).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Publish-size delta zero — no BFF code change.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    The optional `SendEmail` follow-up Action is NOT part of this Template. It's a separate Action (defined elsewhere, possibly task 054's SendEmail Tool reused) surfaced as a follow-up button in the SpaarkeAi result tile. The user explicitly invokes it; that invocation triggers its own `IGateResolver` flow.

    The `SummarizeText` Tool referenced in Step 2 is one of the "always-on" tools or a registered AI Tool — verify its id matches the registered Tool from task 022 (FindResources implementation) before deploying.

    The G2 gate evidence (an interactive E2E run with a real matter) is recorded in `notes/deploys/053-template-summarize-matter.md` and referenced from the `TASK-INDEX.md` "Acceptance Evidence" section. This is the load-bearing piece — without it, the project's overall G2 gate is unverified.

    Per design.md §7.4.5 guardrail #7 (citation discipline): the output schema's `sourceCitations` array is non-optional. The AI `SummarizeText` Tool's response MUST include them. If the dev-environment AI service returns a summary without citations, that's a Tool implementation bug (in task 022's registration) — fix by tightening the Tool's prompt template, not by relaxing the Template's schema.

    Do not duplicate Tool ids across Templates. If `QueryDataverse` is already registered (as expected — it's an always-on foundational Tool from task 052), reference the existing id; do not create a new one.
  </notes>

